claim.claim-text:
1. An address transition detecting circuit comprising: 
a first detecting means for detecting a first transition of an address buffer signal, by which an external address signal is buffered/outputted; 
a first control means for controlling the flow of current of said first detecting means so that the output of said first detecting means has a different phase from and the same pulse width to said address buffer signal; 
a second detecting means for detecting a second transition of said address buffer signal; 
a second control means for controlling the flow of current of said second detecting means so that the output of said second detecting means has a is different phase from and the same pulse width to said address buffer signal; and 
an output means for inverting the output of said first detecting means or the output of said second detecting means to output an address transition detecting signal.

2. The address transition detecting circuit according to claim 1, wherein said first detecting means includes: 
a second inverting means connected to a first inverting means for inverting said address buffer signal, for inverting the output of said first inverting means; 
a first buffering means for stabilizing the output of said second inverting means to a given potential; 
a first delay means for delaying the output of said second inverting means by a given period of time; and 
a third inverting means for inverting the output of said second inverting means.

3. The address transition detecting circuit according to claim 1, wherein said second detecting means includes: 
a fourth inverting means for inverting the output of said first inverting means; 
a fifth inverting means for inverting the output of said fourth inverting means; 
a second buffering means for stabilizing the output of said fifth inverting means; 
a second delay means for delaying the output of said fifth inverting means by a given period of time; and 
a sixth inverting means for inverting the output of said fifth inverting means.

8. An address transition detecting circuit comprising: 
a first detecting means for detecting a first transition of an address buffer signal, by which an external address signal is buffered/outputted; 
a first control means for controlling the flow of current of said first detecting means so that the output of said first detecting means has a different phase from and the same pulse width to said address buffer signal; 
a second detecting means for detecting a second transition of said address buffer signal; 
a second control means for controlling the flow of current of said second detecting means so that the output of said second detecting means has a different phase from and the same pulse width to said address buffer signal; 
a first output means for inverting the output of said first detecting means or the output of said second detecting means to output a first address transition detecting signal; 
a noise removing means for removing a noise included in the first address transition detecting signal; and 
a second output means for inverting the output of said noise removing means to output a second address transition detecting signal.

9. The address transition detecting circuit according to claim 8, wherein said first detecting means includes: 
a second inverting means connected to a first inverting means for inverting said address buffer signal, for inverting the output of said first inverting means; 
a first buffering means for stabilizing the output of said second inverting means to a given potential; 
a first delay means for delaying the output of said second inverting means by a given period of time; and 
a third inverting means for inverting the output of said second inverting means.

10. The address transition detecting circuit according to claim 8, wherein said second detecting means includes: 
a fourth inverting means for inverting the output of said first inverting means; 
a fifth inverting means for inverting the output of said fourth inverting means; 
a second buffering means for stabilizing the output of said fifth inverting means; 
a second delay means for delaying the output of said fifth inverting means by a given period of time; and 
a sixth inverting means for inverting the output of said fifth inverting means.

15. The address transition detecting circuit according to claim 8, wherein said noise removing means includes: 
a third buffering means for receiving first and second bias signals generated by a given bias circuit as an input to stabilize said address transition detection signal; 
an OR gate for logically combining the output of said third buffering means and said first address transition detection signal; 
a seventh inverting means for inverting said first address transition detection signal; and 
a transfer means for transmitting the output of said OR gate or the output of said seventh inverting means to said second output means.

16. The address transition detecting circuit according to claim 15, wherein said third buffering means includes: 
fifth PMOS transistor and sixth PMOS transistor connected between the power supply terminal and the ground terminal and driven by a first bias signal; 
seventh PMOS transistor and seventh NMOS transistor driven by said first address transition detection signal; 
eighth PMOS transistor and eighth NMOS transistor, which are driven by the outputs of said seventh PMOS transistor and said seventh NMOS transistor; and 
ninth NMOS transistor and tenth NMOS transistor, which are driven by a second bias signal.
